# Structure & Naming

The full contract is `docs/vault-contract.md`. This rule states the discipline;
it does not restate the algorithm.

## Non-negotiables

- One folder per PDF; nested folders mirror ToC depth; one note per ToC leaf.
- Branch sections use the **folder-note convention** (a note named after its own
  folder), so every section basename is unique. The only `index.md` in the vault
  is the single vault-root library index.
- Filenames are `<derived-toc-number>-<slug>.md`. The ToC number is **positional**
  (derived from sibling order, zero-padded), never parsed from the title text —
  so preface/appendix/unnumbered entries still get stable numbers.
- Slugify is the pure function in `scripts/lib/slugify.py`. Do not invent a
  different slugging scheme.

## Discipline

- Do not hand-name files in a way that diverges from `compute_paths`
  (`scripts/lib/naming.py`). If you need a different layout, change the contract
  and the harness together, not one note ad hoc.
- Keep the structure deterministic: the same manifest must always yield the same
  paths.

## Forbidden

- A second `index.md` anywhere.
- Bare or title-parsed numbering.
- Diverging from the slug algorithm or the folder-note convention.
